/wiki/FC_Andijon: FC Andijon (Uzbek: Андижон профессионал футбол клуби or Andijon professional futbol klubi, English: professional football club Andijan) is an Uzbekistani football club based in Andijan. the club plays in Uzbek League.
/wiki/Andijan: Andijan (sometimes spelled Andijon or Andizhan in English) (Uzbek: Andijon / Андижон / ئەندىجان; Persian: اندیجان‎, Andijân/Andīǰān; Russian: Андижан, Andižan) is a city in Uzbekistan. It is the administrative, economic, and cultural center of Andijan Region. Andijan is located in the south-eastern edge of the Fergana Valley near Uzbekistan's border with Kyrgyzstan.
/wiki/Soghlom_Avlod_Stadium: Soghlom Avlod Stadium also known as Navruz Stadium is the official home of FK Andijan
/wiki/FC_Dinamo_Samarqand: FC Dinamo Samarqand (Uzbek: Динамо Самарқанд Футбол Клуби, Tajik: Dastai Futboli Dinamo Samarqand, Russian: футбольный клуб "Динамо Самарканд") is an Uzbek football club, based in city of Samarkand, Uzbekistan. Currently it plays in Uzbek League.
/wiki/Samarkand: Samarkand (/ˈsæmərkænd/; Uzbek: Samarqand; Persian: سمرقند‎; Russian: Самарканд), alternatively Samarqand, is a city in south-eastern Uzbekistan and one of the oldest continuously inhabited cities in Central Asia. There is evidence of human activity in the area of the city from the late Paleolithic era, though there is no direct evidence of when Samarkand was founded; some theories propose that it was founded between the 8th and 7th centuries B.C. Prospering from its location on the Silk Road between China and the Mediterranean, at times Samarkand was one of the greatest cities of Central Asia.
/wiki/Dinamo_Samarkand_Stadium: Dinamo Stadium is a multi-use stadium in Samarkand, Uzbekistan. It is currently used mostly for football matches and is the home stadium of Dynamo Samarkand.
/wiki/FK_Istiqlol_Fergana: Istiqlol futbol klubi is an Uzbekistani football club based in Fergana. The club plays in Uzbekistan Pro League.
/wiki/Fergana: Fergana (Uzbek: Fargʻona/Фарғона, فەرغانە; Tajik: Фарғона, Farğona/Farƣona; Persian: فرغانه‎ Farġāna/Farqâna; Russian: Фергана́), or Ferghana, is the capital of Fergana Region in eastern Uzbekistan.  Fergana is about 420 km east of Tashkent, about 75 km west of Andijan, and less than 20 km from the Kyrgyzstan border.
/wiki/Xorazm_FK_Urganch: Xorazm FK Urganch is a Uzbekistani football club based in Urganch. They play in the second level in Uzbekistani football.
/wiki/Urgench: Urgench (Uzbek: Urganch, Ургeнч, ئۇرگەنج‎; Persian: گرگانج‎, Gorgånch/Gorgānč/Gorgânc) is a city in western Uzbekistan. The population of Urgench on April 24, 2014 was approximately 150,110, an increase from 139,100 in 1999. It is the capital of the Khorezm Region, on the Amu Darya River and the Shavat canal. The city is situated 450 km (280 mi) west of Bukhara across the Kyzylkum Desert.
/wiki/Xorazm_Stadium: Xorazm Stadium is a multi-use stadium in Urgench, Uzbekistan.  It is currently used mostly for football matches and is the home stadium of Xorazm FK Urganch.  The stadium holds 25,000 people.
/wiki/FK_Mash'al_Mubarek: FC Mashʼal Mubarek (Uzbek: Машъал  Муборак профессионал футбол клуби, Russian: Футбольный клуб Машъал Мубарек) is an Uzbek is an Uzbekistan football club based in Mubarek, Uzbekistan.
/wiki/Muborak: Muborak (sometimes spelled Mubarek in English) (Uzbek: Muborak/Муборак; Tajik: Муборак; Russian: Мубарек) is a small city located in Qashqadaryo Region of Uzbekistan. The city is the administrative center of Muborak District.
/wiki/Bahrom_Vafoev_Stadium: Bahrom Vafoev Stadium is a multi-use stadium in Mubarek, Uzbekistan.  It is currently used mostly for football matches and serves as the home for Mash'al Mubarek, an Uzbeki football club.  The stadium holds 11,000 people.
/wiki/Khakkulabad: Khakkulabad (Uzbek: Xaqqulobod/Хаққулобод, Russian: Хаккулабад) is a town in Namangan Region, Uzbekistan. It is the administrative center of Naryn District, Uzbekistan. The town population in 1989 year was 19926 people.
/wiki/FK_Orol_Nukus: FC Orol Nukus (Uzbek: Орол Нукус футбол клуби) is Uzbekistani football club based in Nukus. Currently it plays in Uzbekistan First League.
/wiki/Nukus: Nukus (Uzbek: Nukus, Нукус; Karakalpak: Nókis, Нөкис; Kazakh: Núkis; Russian: Нукус) is the sixth-largest city in Uzbekistan, and the capital of the Republic of Karakalpakstan. The population of Nukus as of January 1, 2018 was approximately 312,100. The Amu Darya river passes west of the town.
/wiki/FC_Shurtan_Guzar: FC Shurtan Guzar (Uzbek: Sho'rtan G'uzor professional futbol klubi or Шўртан Ғузор футбол клуби, Russian: Футбольный клуб Шуртан Гузар) is an Uzbek football club based in G‘uzor, Uzbekistan.
/wiki/G\u2018uzor: G‘uzor also spelled as Guzar (Uzbek: G‘uzor / Ғузoр; Russian: Гузар; Tajik: Гузор; Persian: گذار‎) is a town in Qashqadaryo Region of Uzbekistan. It serves as the administrative center of Guzar District. The town population in 1989 year was 17,253 people.
/wiki/G'uzor_Stadium: G'uzor Stadium is the main stadium of the hometown club FC Shurtan Guzar. It has been recently renovated.[when?]
/wiki/Termez: Termez (Uzbek: Termiz/Термиз; Russian: Термез; Tajik: Тирмиз; Persian: ترمذ‎ Termez, Tirmiz; Arabic: ترمذ‎ Tirmidh; Ancient Greek Tàrmita, Thàrmis, Θέρμις) is a city in the southernmost part of Uzbekistan near the Hairatan border crossing of Afghanistan. It is  the hottest point of Uzbekistan. It has a population of 140,404 (1 January 2005), and is the capital of Surxondaryo Region.
/wiki/Uzbekistan_Pro_League: Uzbekistan Pro League (Uzbek: O'zbekiston Pro ligasi or Ўзбекистон Про лигаси)— football League in Uzbekistan, the second level of importance after the Uzbekistan Super League in the national championship.
